This paper discusses the development of a digital object repository system for libraries, which involves the use of web-based technologies such as XML and Web services. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), databases (cs.DB), cyberinfrastructure (cs.CY), and software engineering (cs.SE). However, given the focus on digital libraries and repository architecture, cs.DL is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.IR and cs.DB.
